text.paragraph:
Inform patients to take Amoxicillin and Clavulanate Potassium (600 mg/42.9 mg) for Oral Suspension every 12 hours with a meal or snack to reduce the possibility of gastrointestinal upset. If diarrhea develops and is severe or lasts more than 2 or 3 days, they should call their doctor 
  [see Dosage and Administration (
                     2.1
                     ), Warnings and Precautions (
                     5.5
                     )].
